#: ../../../filesystems/smb/cifsroot.rst:11
msgid ""
"The CONFIG_CIFS_ROOT option enables experimental root file system support "
"over the SMB protocol via cifs.ko."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/smb/cifsroot.rst:14
msgid ""
"It introduces a new kernel command-line option called 'cifsroot=' which will "
"tell the kernel to mount the root file system over the network by utilizing "
"SMB or CIFS protocol."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/smb/cifsroot.rst:18
msgid ""
"In order to mount, the network stack will also need to be set up by using "
"'ip=' config option. For more details, see Documentation/admin-guide/nfs/"
"nfsroot.rst."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/smb/cifsroot.rst:22
msgid ""
"A CIFS root mount currently requires the use of SMB1+UNIX Extensions which "
"is only supported by the Samba server. SMB1 is the older deprecated version "
"of the protocol but it has been extended to support POSIX features (See "
"[1]). The equivalent extensions for the newer recommended version of the "
"protocol (SMB3) have not been fully implemented yet which means SMB3 doesn't "
"support some required POSIX file system objects (e.g. block devices, pipes, "
"sockets)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/smb/cifsroot.rst:30
msgid ""
"As a result, a CIFS root will default to SMB1 for now but the version to use "
"can nonetheless be changed via the 'vers=' mount option.  This default will "
"change once the SMB3 POSIX extensions are fully implemented."
msgstr ""

